reviews.text: Arrived by coach with a group and no problems off loading. Reception staff well organized and we we're in our room in no time. Allocated room a bit dated but clean and airy. Nice large television in room,with usual tea, coffee  facilities. Fridge with mini bar and treats for a price. Breakfast was adequate with staff happy to help. Restaurant for evening meals if you wish. Situated only 25 minutes walk to Circular Quay and only 5 minutes to Hyde Park. Gym and roof top pool available.

Conveniently located within walking distance to lots of shops and places to eat. Clean, well lit room. Comfortable bed and very large bathroom. Safe, ironing board & iron; coffee pot and more. Friendly staff. I enjoyed my stay.

Trendy apartment in good condition. Modern entertainment (eg Chromecast enabled TV) and pleasantly furnished. Room service and mini bar market priced. Gym, pool and sauna on site - good condition. Bathroom nicely appointed though the bath/shower combination in my room was dated. 3 stars for being as expected, +1 for furnishings and room ambience - very comfortable and modern.

Lovely place, conveniently located for CBD and Hyde Park, good facilities, big room with great bed and modern decor. Staff extremely helpful and welcoming. Mentioned it was our honeymoon and a basket of fruit and sparkling wine was delivered to our room. We had a great stay.

RENOVATIONS! No pool, foyer in a horrid state. Would have liked to have known these renovations were taking place BEFORE arrival. View from high-level room was pleasant, photo attached. Furnishings were pleasant, minimal and modern, however shower pressure was a no. Lots of mirrors, air conditioner goes very cold and is high powered. Staff were great, and cleaning service was consistent. Very convenient location, near museum station, and good cafes near. WiFi worked well on phone.

Good location hotel if you are a tourist visitor to Sydney as it is near to the Museum railway station which in only a couple of stops to the harbour. We had to change rooms due to problems but the reception staff were first class and we ended up in a much larger room with a good view. All rooms have a small kitchenette with kettle, microwave, coffee and tea. The beds are comfortable but I could not get used to the pillows. The breakfast if you have paid for it is buffet style with a good selection of hot and cold food stuffs to choose from. You certainly won't go out hungry. A good hotel in a great location.
Hotel location is great, close to Museum Train Station when travelling from the Airport, just 5-8mins. Handy to all tourist spots and walking distance to bus stop. Helpful staff. Would stay again.
Pretty basic hotel close to Museum Station. Good breakfast at a reasonable price. Good staff. Held our luggage until after lunch on the day we checked out.
Shower has no water pressure. There is other people's pubic hair in the bathroom behind the door. Bed is nice but and the AC works well.

Room 1021 is definitely not great even for a single night stay ($159). Check in was good & front desk staff at the time was helpful. After that all downhill. Air conditioning does not work at all. When reported to front desk it took several follow up for a person to come up & check. When someone turned up, she looked like she tried fixing the problem to no avail; kept us awake & promised to call back when fixed but didn’t. No explanation offered at all. Just seems it is standard complaint. The room looks dated. Bathroom door water damaged as well as the fixtures. Carpet a bit dirty but room has no apparent smell & everything looks clean. Definitely won’t be coming back & not recommended at all.

Amazing experience! Beautiful day to see this stunning piece of architecture! Didn't go in but just walking outside is one hell of an experience! Beautiful large walking spaces overlooking the harbour in every direction, great restaurants underneath and not far away in circular quay, easy to get to and beautiful park nearby to relax. Have been here 4-5 times and love it every time. A must see when in Sydney!

Perhaps the most visited tourist attraction in NSW. It’s the icon of Sydney, if you haven’t been here, you haven’t been into Sydney. It’s just like that.
If you’re interested in watching performance, check the schedule it is available online too. I like this place in the morning, less tourists and still have a beautiful shot of the opera house. Best getting its “postcard” view from The Domain.
Or crossing to Manly beach from the harbour? Can do.

What can I say about the opera house that hasn't been already said. Many people travel to Sydney because of this iconic building and there is nothing to be disappointed about. It looks beautiful with the bridge and harbour as a backdrop. You can take pictures from many different angles and get different results. One the one hand it reminds me of the giant Orchid Temple in Delhi but then it also reminds me of an armadillo I think. But seeing it up close was very rewarding and it was one of the highlights for me and I didn't even go inside!

Sydney Opera House is a famous building well known around the world. We did the guided tour which was amazing. Always busy with lots of tourists and locals who are just visiting or have bought tickets to one of the many shows that the Opera House has to offer. You haven't seen Sydney unless you visit the Opera House!

Whether you're looking at it from a distance or enjoying an orchestral masterpiece on the inside, the Sydney Opera House is definitely a must visit destination at least once in your life. Not only is it gorgeous at daytime, with plenty of food and drink options in the surrounding area, many of the ferries operate at night and can provide you with views such as the picture I have taken (the picture really doesn't do it justice though).

result.formatted_address: Blue Mountains, New South Wales, Australia
result.name: Blue Mountains

reviews.text: The Blue Mountains are absolutely stunning! We arrived on a slightly overcast day but that still doesn't take away from the breathtaking views however as the day went on the clouds lifted and the views are something to behold. You have to see them in person to really appreciate how vast it is. The blue mountains are a must visit for all ages!

Classic touristic site of Australia. Must see. Tons of things to do from walks, wine, great food, historic landmarks. The views are incredible and some great group tours available too. Bring water and comfortable shoes. Some hotels are fantastic with the stunning views provided by the area. Locals are very friendly too.

One time trip is a good lot of story and nature time , if you are a tourist and is here for few week you can skip. 

Ideal for trekking, nature lovers .

Hop on Hop off bus available right at station . Got some adventure rides ... prefer getting $89 pass for all sites . 

Do reach early in morning if you want to cover all.

I am from mountains and I Love mountains.
This is the nearest place from Sydney to see mountains.
I would rather call them hills i don’t know if that’s justified.
The thing is when you reach there you are at its top and you are looking at mountains below you.
They look bluish and very beautiful but that’s not something how I have seen mountains normally.
I enjoyed short hikes and been there a couple of times.
Highly Recommend!

The Blue Mountains is a rugged region west of Sydney in Australia’s New South Wales. Known for dramatic scenery, it encompasses steep cliffs, eucalyptus forests, waterfalls and villages dotted with guesthouses, galleries and gardens. You will need 2 days to visit all the attraction in Blue mountain. 1 bus is running to get you thru all attraction.

Way better than USYD! Only downside is it will be tough and fast-paced from week 1 because the uni transitioned to a new trimester system instead of traditional two semesters. Therefore, there will be only 10 weeks to go through the entire course materials instead of 13 weeks.

University is perfect but thought I would meet international students and get international experience before I came here. Now this place is like biggest china town in Australia. The only language I hear in all of my classes is Chinese except from lecturer. It’s very hard for me to make friends. I'm doing Master. During tutorial classes, some Chinese tutors walk to Chinese students tables and TEACH IN CHINESE !!!!!!
I love being a UNSW student! Fantastic lecturers
Great University, especially caters to Engineering degrees

UNSW has a unique focus on the scientific, technological and professional disciplines. It offers an extensive range of undergraduate, postgraduate and research programs. A perfect place for student to boost up their career.

This is a complicated hotel.  The location is fantastic, right in the middle of the Rocks.  The view from room 608 was incredible - both the Opera House and the bridge.  The bed was very comfortable and  housekeeping did a good job of making up the room.  The lobby was nicely decorated and front desk staff friendly and efficient.  The room, however, was a big disappointment.  The walls were scratched, paint missing, gouges out of the door mouldings and the kitchenette was last renovated a long time ago.  The advertised mini bar was completely missing and the coffee maker was a tea kettle with packets of instant coffee.  We paid $440AU with the advanced purchase and member discounts.  I know the Rocks is an expensive area but this did not feel like a reasonable rate for a room in such bad condition.

Very centrally placed in the Rock. Easily accessible from the port and the rail station. Great kitchenettes with microwave, fridge with a small freezer, and a cook top. Our only negative: watch out when taking a shower, very! Slippery.
Fantastic location. A little worn. Security could be improved by not sending visitors up to the rooms without checking with the guests
The welcoming staff elevate this hotel above others in the area: they seem genuinely pleased to see you, take time to know you beyond the check in process. Will never hesitate to return here
Staff were very friendly and helpful. Great location. We were upgraded to one of their terrace rooms which was great. We think we will use this hotel as our go to spot when we are in Sydney.
Meriton Suites was great.  Spacious and clean with everything one could want for a self-catering stay.  Conveniently close to a supermarket and bus routes into downtown Sydney.
The staff were beyond amazing! The rooms were gorgeous, so nice and clean! We had a lovely stay and will definitely be back! Definitely recommend this place :)

Meriton Waterloo is well worth a visit or stay. Caters to both long and short term stays.  Summary is that it is extremely well equipped compared to a hotel room at a very very reasonable price. 
Rooms are much better than a hotel room and come with full kitchen. Rooms are fully furnished to a very high standard. Most have balcony. Wifi is fast.  Parking is available on site for a small fee.  
Numerous ( free for guests )facilities within complex , including fitness centre, indoor pool, spa etc located a short walk 
Staff are very helpful and friendly.  A special mention for both Tatiana and Jessica who represent Meriton in such a friendly, efficient and courteous manner. 
Location is very good.  Central to many needs of travellers.  Handy to Sydney airport. Meriton Waterloo comes very highly recommended to those who desire to stay somewhere, where no doubt their expectations will be exceeded, and at a price that is surprisingly low for a place of such quality.

Great value. Although located on a quite noisy stretch of road rooms are up to date, functional and all inclusive (kettle, microwave, stove, pots/pans etc) and are a great value alternative to a hotel/airbnb.

Rooms have double glazing in bedrooms so noise is tolerable (we were on quite a high floor though) - and there are rooms that face away from the road. Nice views of Moore Park and the golf course from 9th floor and up.

Would stay again.

Great location, large and clean suites with all amenities for business and leisure travellers. 

Dedicated and smiling staff who have made my two weeks stay a very comfortable one! Special thanks to Jessica and Tatiana for their profesionalism and kindness. 

I higlhy recommend this place. Can't wait to go back.

Beautiful view from the top balcony. Great value for money, close to everything you need. All sorts of food shops available in walking distance. Lovely staff members, as well as the cleaning staff. Highly recommend.

Good service is good when all goes according to plan. Unfortunately I messed up my booking, but Daren and Stephanie rescued the situation with remarkable grace and efficiency. Our stay was beyond expectations. Strongly recommend Coogee Sands. Michael
Clean, fresh and neat rooms and very friendly staff. Good roof top terrace. Close to amenities. A nice place to stay.

If you want to be 100 metres from Coogee beach then this is the place for you. This spot is right in the hub of it all. Walking distance to local shops and close to everything you need. We chose this accommodation because it included a car space (subject to availability). We stayed on a weekend & didn't have an issues. There was ample parking. Reception was attentive and came to the rescue with a sewing kit when I needed a safety pin for my dress. Highly recommended.

The staff are very nice. The place is right on the beach. The neighborhood of coogee is lovely. Otherwise the place has nothing to recommend itself. It is very old and dingy feeling. Just feels kind of gross. The walls are paper thin so you hear everything going on in your neighbor’s room. It is right next to a bunch of very loud night clubs and you hear everything. Besides the noise you can’t open the windows because you’ll smell all kind of restaurant smells that are not necessarily u pleasant but not what you want to fill your room with. The place does have working air conditioning units. Any kind of view is completely blocked by buildings.

Staying here at the moment. Clean. Quiet. Close to local buses and some super restaurants and cafes. Staff helpful and friendly. Sweet little pool and garden area. Air con and free WiFi. Private bathroom, coffee facilities. Perfect for a short break.
Good place. Rooms were a little small and basic but comfortable and the service was good. Good location with resturants and cafes near by
Great place to stay if you're into nightlife. Very friendly staff and clean room.

I stayed there in 1997 when it was called Sullivan's. It was a basic room and staff okay except for the moody receptionist but she's probably gone now and the hotel is likely under new management. The standard room in the photo hasn't upgraded much since 1997.
Staff were competent and very helpful.

I had such a great time here. Was supposed to stay for 4 days and ended up staying for 3 weeks. All the people is what makes the hostel. Really likes all the free trips that was going on and the bar has a fun night out every night. Can recommend

Fun and social hostel with a lot going on. Luna in reception helped me with my travels and she was very helpful. I genuinely feel like she cared that I had a good trip and also gave me a great deal. 

The hostel was also great with free activities almost everyday!

Great location and staff. They have free day trips going out every week like bus to bronte with free food and goon. they go to manly and the pool. And it's all free. I think that's such a great thing to have in a hostel and more hostel should be like this.

Have thoroughly enjoyed my stay here at Base Hostel. I had a very satisfactory room with remarkably comfortable beds for a hostel equaling in a great night sleep! I would complain that the kitchen was too busy for my liking but I guess it just shows the popularity of this hostel! Well deserved 4*

Very nice hostel. Comfortable room and I was able to move to a room that suited me with no problems. Staff helped me with my needs and told me great things to do in the city as i am new to Sydney. 5 stars.

We had a great stay here. The staff at the reception are professional but still friendly. We stayed in a 2 bedroom 2 bathroom apartment. Everything was nice and clean. The apartment was very well equipped. We enjoyed our stay and would highly recommend it to others.

We stayed for 2 weeks. We are the kind of people who do not need housekeeping everyday. We can use the bath towels 3 days in a row, do not need our bed made everyday, nor the room swept everyday.

But they would call on the days we did not call for anything... like maybe we need new towels, more complimentary coffee, or any service.

We had the unit with a small kitchenette and we are so happy to have it when we want to prepare meals. Kitchenette is stocked with most things you need... well, except for soup bowls... hint to management :-)

Place is but in the pricey side but was clean and well equipped. The living room, was a good size with a lounge, dining area and a study area. Bedroom had a double wardrobe, bathroom had a bath and a seperate shower with a laundry area with washing machine and dryer. The kitchen was in the living room, cooker has 4 gas hobs. It is a little dated but doesn’t look too bad.

Had a great experience here with a couple of friends here. Great hotel space and the view was just amazing...good to get together with friends and family or just a loved one to get away for the weekend have a few drink or just to eat and relax great to just spend quality time here.

Nice if you get a view and a decent rate. We were first offered a room looking out onto a wall. But the second choice was great.. Till the rate went through the roof and it was cheaper to move to a 5 start waterfront room at the Pullman.

I had a great stay here. Great location. I was able to check-in hours before the designated time. Nice room, comfy bed and linen, cozy lighting, furniture and fixtures. The breakfast buffet can be better, though, for this hotel's level and price. The breakfast lounge is also dark and confined, not exactly a great place to greet and start the day.

Great value and an excellent location close to plenty of places to eat and public transport if required.
Their gym is truly excellent, it seems more like a full function gym than a hotel gym so well done on getting this spot on. Also a sweet pool to swim in after.
Will be back and could become the regular place to stay in Sydney

This is my favourite hotel - always nice and helpful staff. Great deals and discounts with my free membership. The Suites are modern and have plenty of space and they are Right in the heart of the city and can access their overnight parking too. Well done to the Fraser Suites Sydney 🙌🏼

Love this place great friendly and helpful staff. My room was upgraded to the penthouse top floor 2 big rooms 2 bathrooms upstairs and down stairs lounge room, dining area and a fully equipped kitchen beautiful design for the 3 nights amazing city view. Ordered room service it was  5 star quality. Location is  perfect for public transportation, high end and low end shopping stores and a variety of restaurants to choose from I highly recommend Frasers Suites.
Beautiful stuff And very helpful When I got there the  Computers were down and  The girls gave me a free upgrade For a few minutes.it was a great experience, definitely staying there again

Really happy with the stay. Apartments are clean and spacious. Only negative is no free parking. Loads to do around world tower. A shopping centre literally below the building. Great restaurants and cafes in any direction. You can walk to any other area of the CBD quite easily
Great view from room. Nice staff and very willing to help. However no room service attended (make bed etc) at all for a two night stay, not sure if this is normal.

Great location, Staff very pleasant and welcoming.  Very large apartment. Magnificent views for Darling Harbour.  Definitely would stay here again. Pool Spa and sauna great facilities. very relaxing before our cruise

What a disappointment!  The bedding had holes & stains in second room. The air conditioning was not blowing out any air (very stuffy) we asked for a room with 2 single beds (not a king size bed!) for 2 teenagers. Mold in the corners in the master bathroom. Very hard mattress, whould have had a better sleep on the floor. Over priced for what we expected.
Had the 3 bedroom with 6 beds on level 75, spectacular view. Was not enough drinking glasses in the room, but a quick call and they were delivered within a few minutes. Excellent room!!

Friendly helpful staff. Clean room. Nice bathroom gels etc. lovely pool. Close to great eating places, city. Queen Vic building which I love to visit. Good kitchenette but no microwave or pans in room. Decor bit dated but that's minor point. Had a lovely stay. Definitely value for money & will return.

A great overnight stay at the Radisson. The room was spacious and clean. The staff were very friendly. Buffet breakfast was lovely with a good variety of food. The location was great. Close to darling harbour. Would definitely stay again
Great location, close to ICC.  next door to BBQ king.  Nice rooms, friendly staff.  Always good for an overnight stay in Sydney. Will stay again.
Decent location, friendly service. Suite was big but quite dated in design.
Good location with large rooms. Dated furnishings and sparsely decorated. Kind of shabby. Kitchen had minimal dishes no glasses or cups

This is a good hotel in a great location. Staff are friendly and welcoming. The bed is very comfortable. Rooms are very stylish but sadly that's also where some of the challenges lay. Nowhere to hang a towel, lighting very dim. This is the second time I've stayed here and I still enjoyed it. Just wish someone thought about the practicalities as well as the style.
Cool eclectic place to stay right in the heart of Sydney.  Room was perfect staff wonderful. Great setting to have a meal or cocktail. Highly recommended

Hands down the best hotel I have stayed at, and I stay at a lot of hotels. The staff greet you before you even make it through the door, and are incredibly helpful and give a brunch of pointers / local tips. Lobby & rooms are really stylish and theres always great music playing.

I wouldn't dream of staying anywhere else when in Sydney.

It's funny how much good staff effects your experience. It is already such a beautiful & cool venue & then the staff just took it to the next level. The perfect blend of friendly & professional. Oh yes & the bed... the comfiest I've slept in! Looking forward to coming back! Try the truffle eggs.

Great location.. Easy to get to public transport systems.. Nice coffee and grab n go breakfast in foyer.. Friendly staff.. Hotel was clean and tidy.. Room was just a bit smaller than picture depicted on website. Would stay again.

Had the best night here. A beautiful place to stay kid free. Love the blackout shades and the spa was fantastic. So many great spots to get a drink and something to eat. The executive lounge is a big bonus and worth the extra money to stay in a executive room. Can't wait for our next visit.

Excellent location between George and Pitt Street. Reception staff very good and nice hall in general. The swimming pool can be cured more but it’s part of a free service given by a third party. The breakfast is worth the money and the staff is also there very good. 
The rooms need an update. 
In the end, I can suggest it for a short stay.

Sales pitch - ended up with increasing my room rate by 30% for equal, if not inferior presenting room. Won't be using exec lounge. Carpet in upgraded room not similar to 1970s suburban Brisbane. Not very smart, Hilton. Might consider better English speakers at reception please.

Upmarket hotel with good Hilton standards. Restaurant is stunning, with huge glass cabinets of wine looming over the room and good views onto the QVB building opposite. A great place to start the day with breakfast. Location wise you couldn't get more central. Good executive lounge as well.

I would have given 5 stars had George Street not been turned into a construction site! Hilton still got the best hotel location in town but lobby is getting so crowded that you will only enjoy staying inside your room. Loads of homeless guys asking you for cigarettes right next to a 5-star hotel entrance is just unpleasant......

Pizzas are crispy and sizzling with flavour. Atmosphere was a bit too clean when we went but perhaps 6pm was a bit early for dinner. Prices weren't too bad, about the average for restaurant quality pizzas. Service was attentive and friendly. 
Delicious fare and good selection of drinks. 
Once the well overdue tram construction is over on Anzac Pde this will be a real night out.

Had come in for an all you can eat night. However, all of us had to wait ages for food. Left the place hungry. We were also overcharged for the night for unusual reasons. Talking to staff was like talking to robots.
Honestly,  just my mother can cook faster and better than these restaurant staff combined.
It was such lovely place to eat amazing food and great price lovely peope also! 10/10

Overpriced and dishonest, the restaurant that has so much 'acclaim' did not live up to expectations befitting a 4 star rating.

Staff were aloof, uncommunicative, and brusque in the treatment of our large group booked for 'all you can eat'. The only thing that we were full of at the end of our meal was dissatisfaction and supreme disappointment. Charging extra for hidden costs linked to children, as well as alluding to the need for a cash only payment, the kitchen stated that there was no more food left, and had the audacity to leave uncooked pizza dough sitting visibly on the counter.

I would recommend people think twice, or even thrice before being lured in by fancy aquatic decorations and white tablecloths. You only need to look across the road on the corner to find better service.

Terrible experience. Took a group of people there and mistreated. Random overcharge for children meals all you can eat. Miscounted the amount of guests we had. Food service was so slow, i was still hungry even though it was an 'all you can eat'. Recommend to never come to this restaurant.

Not sure if this Subway has changed management of late or what, but a lot, if not all, of the staff have changed recently and it's nowhere near as good as it used to be. I recently went in and the guy that made my sandwich was literally wearing headphones and over the course of my order he managed to stuff up at least 6 things that I had to correct him on. Maybe take your headphones out and you'll be able to hear me properly dude. Smh

I can't stand the smell of this place
I hate the fact that it's impossible to walk past the shop without smelling it. To me, it's a form of pollution.
I realise not everyone will agree.
Just my opinion
I have no problem with the business, I have no problem with people enjoying their food.
I just wish I didn't have to smell it
Perfect thanks again for your attention to detail with you ordered sandwich through uber eats you still got everything A1 + perfect in the Package...
My daughter love to have tack a way from subway
Everything was perfect there keep it up

Had a craving after an epic study session, so at 2am I got myself a large quarter pounder meal. Usually I regret ordering McDonald's after eating, but this time I did not! Fries were very fresh, burger spot on and coke great (better than from a can).👍⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

MacDonalds was very busy and this maybe why I rated it down to 3. It wasn't the crowds waiting but the fries we ordered were not up to their usual crispiness but soggy and limp. I suspect the large turnover of the frozen chips going through the frier the oil had ultimately cooled off and not got to its ultimate cooking temperature.
Service as usual was very good, staff meeting and greeting and serving all had a welcoming smile. No issues.

Sunday, 09/03/19 I placed an order for spicy double Mc chicken... The burgers were stale, smelly and bread was not soft. I am regular customer who often have lunch after uni... but today I had the worst experience.
Don't visit on weekends especially on Sundays. Service is great.

The place is spacious and food delivery is quick.  The staff is friendly and polite. Wheelchair access and children playing area is available. Ambiance is good and value for money. Visit if you want to visit good Mcdonald.
Lively ambience even at midnight. On a weekday! Sympathetic to the staffs coz this place is super busy.
Very authentic and tasty Vietnamese food and there is a lot of it!  Being BYO helps as well.  The staff are very friendly and helpful. Try the pancake or the steamed/deep fried snapper!! Yum!

Nice quick service, clean and bright surroundings and food was tasty, tried the seafood laksa it looked and tasted yummy... not as hot as I like it but I should’ve mentioned that to the waiter... however I was disappointed slightly with the amount of seafood and noodles I received, a few slices of fish, slivers of squid and 4 maybe 5 small prawns didn’t satisfy my palate and I was left wanting more partly because of the taste and partly because of the lack of volume... would I eat there again? Yes... just maybe try some other dish
Good soup and usually good pho. Great service though.

A very nice place located at a convenient distance from the bus stop. You can miss this place while walking down the road. But the noise from the crowd will pull you back. We went for dinner at this place and had ordered Chicken Pho and Chicken fried rice... Food was average. Would give 3/5 for the fried rice and 4/5 for the pho
Staff was very friendly and were prompt in taking our order. Ambience was decent and the people kept the place buzzzzzing...
Probably the best pho in the eastern suburbs. Other side dishes are great,  too!
Really tasty ..but order online to avoid long wait times
I live in Bronte and frequently use Randwick pizza hut for picking up Pizza. Better than going to Bondi Beach. Staff is good. Once my order was entered twice, staff was kind to issue refund.

Waitress thought he was some sort of bouncer with that personality he had and the pizzas were thinner than A4 paper and extremenly expensive. for 50 dollars you might has well buy 10 pizzas at ceasars or pizza hut instead of here for 2 a4 paper pizzas

Ordered my first pizza, because of this offer "Buy One Get One FREE" with my 2 mates. I clicked on the promotion banner and ordered the pizza. I checked out, and went to collect my pizza, thinking that I will get two, but I was only offered one. I explained how I ordered, and that there is nothing mentioned about 'FREE' pizza. They talked, and I waited there for my second pizza only to find manager spending 10 minutes on a call to get a new order,  although 3 other staff were standing doing nothing. I stood there waiting for 10 minutes, again asked politely, if I were getting my free pizza, only to get his response that he can't do anything about the website, it is working fine. He didn't offer me the second pizza or any form of compensation even though I mentioned it was my first customer experience with pizzahut. He was plain rude, and didn't seem to care. I had to return with my pizza, could not have it because, it was cold and gross, and ordered from dominos for my mates.
Haven't had a pizza from Pizza Hut in about 15 years, decided to see if in that period of time it improved in any way 😞😞😞 will try again in another 15 years 😁😁😁

We went there Saturday evening, it was full and very busy. Food was good but It was much better when we went there last time. Anyways, we enjoyed our dinner, my wife was happy. And you know happy wife happy life.

Food was quite nice and the servings were large for a very reasonable price, but nothing spectacular. The service could have been better. We went as a large group (12 people) and the servers left before everyone ordered. The place wasn't even that busy but about 4 of us had to wait until the servers came with the other people's food before the rest could order. The servers were also generally unapproachable. Not rude or anything, but could be better.

Food is tasty, well prepared and served reasonably fast, which are main positive points. Unfortunately no alcohol available and that feeling of service like sit down-eat-get lost makes it still average eatery. I'llcome back just for food!

The quantity was great, the food authentic and delicious and the staff were quite friendly. If the beautiful interior isn't enough, the speed the food is given makes you want to both recommend it to others and come here again and again. It's an Uber Eats location and to add to all of this, it's halal. An amazing restaurant, family friendly, it is something you definitely need to tell others about. Thai restaurants are common, but there's a difference between a good restaurant and a stunner.

Solid Thai food with fast and prompt service. Food here is always really consistent and the service is usually fast. It is a popular place so during peak hours it might be busy with some waiting time to grab a table. Would highly recommend for some good Thai cuisine.
Staff is friendly and helpful. Food is okay for a fast food joint. Good value for money.
Yummy chips but I don’t really like the chicken there.
Look. It's oporto. It is what it is. Not bad.
Very quick service and classic Oporto food. All together great

Wish I could give this a 0, staff are clueless. Me and my girlfriend both had a code for a free half chicken, went to the shop which was about 30 minutes away, got there and said I had to download the app to activate it, which is fine. However the app and to verify your account is impossible we tried for 30 minutes then gave my phone to the staff to try, which they were trying for 30 minutes. So we were there for an hour waiting and at no point the manager on site said sorry for the inconvenience let me take your reference number and I'll sort it with head office Monday. None of that after another 10 minutes of her twiderling her thumbs she said there was nothing that she could do, bunch of clueless idiots. We walked out because we didn't want to give any money to this store on principal.

Amazing experience and a Singapore highlight. Excellent food with some innovative combinations which are visually delightful. Service helpful and friendly. Views are spectacular both during the day and at night. Their craft beer is fresh with a good range.

Beautiful view. Was able to reserve a table on the balcony for dinner, and wasn’t pushed at any point to leave or order more which was lovely. Excellent food and drinks. Was lucky to be able to see a concert in addition to the light shows. Other diners were really respectful when coming over to take photos of the view thankfully. Only disappointing thing was the staff didn’t acknowledge our special occasion at all (honeymoon) even though it was in the reservation information. Even just a “congratulations” would have been lovely!

I had expected more but yes it was a good experience albeit very expensive!
The rents must be exorbitant to justify the price of the drinks.
Food was acceptable. Good to view the Marina Bay light show of an evening but don't go to the ladies’ loo. It was filthy and smelt. In a restaurant of this standard one expects more.

Very nice rooftop bar with amazing views. I think it had the best views of the city and their drinks are quite unique and tasty. They have their own brewery and the service staff is quite nice. Would recommend anyone to go here.

We went at happy hour about 2pm and it was a perfect time. They gave us a great seat on the deck. We thought the price was quite good for a beer flight, especially considering alcohol prices in Singapore are very high. Wheat and Bach were the beer highlights, as was the Seattle Beer Cocktail. They also had free wifi!

Awesome place to visit! What a beautiful structure man has ever built. Simply marvellous! This building is stunning and looks even more gorgeous in the evening or night. Laser guided show make this building one of its kind. Evening or night is the best time to visit.

Wow such an amazing experience just being here and this hotel makes it even better. It is absolutely gorgeous and is connected to a mall with such great shopping stores. The architecture of this hotel is like no other and the rooftop pool is breathtaking. Definitely a must see experience

Marina Bay Sands is wonderful. I saw it from outside but I have a wish to go to top floor. I want to see the world largest swimming pool. It’s a iconic tower of Singapore. It looks very beautiful in the evening time. It’s nice to watch the tree light show and water show. Water show is the most attractive show.

Love the place. Relatively less crowded  compared to other shopping centres. There are only one halal restaurant in this area. The Science Art Museum is nearby. Casinos are just around the corner. Great laser light shows at night.

Have a good time here. The booking is pretty good for the larger suites, walk in and the suites are open to you. Walk out, and they’ll close the account for you. No need to do anything. Just keep them within your plans when you come to Singapore.
If u want fun, Sentosa is the place to be at. Experience FUN in all dimensions.
Beautiful island. A bit touristy place but worth a  visit specialty overnight.
Good place for a day. Can walk to the beach and return by free train. Cable cars are also available.
Went to the beach and had nice views. Relaxed and chilled vibe
Such range of activities available on this entertainment paradise. Theyve created the place with such perfection

This is a really fun concept that not many places have. We enjoyed the live show and the tram ride, though if you're going on a busy day the line for the tram could get very long. There are a lot of food and gift areas if you want that as well. This is obviously fun for kids but they have a lot of adult-oriented activities too. A great place to visit if you're 5 or 55. Or any age!

A "must visit" for everyone! Still possibly the best night safari zoo in the world. First take the tram ride for an introduction and to get a feeling of how large the grounds are. Then select your own night safari walk on the trails which have the animals that interest you the most. Take your time so that you can enjoy the experience. Great service because the staff are all friendly & helpful.

The tram ride is the most enjoyable and exciting trip.  The wild night creature show is also interesting and fun for both kids and adults. The food albeit on the high side but served tasty and in quite large portion.  Staff were also friendly and approachable making your trip wonderful and unforgettable.

There's something almost magical about what the night Safari is. It's a chance to see animals in their natural habitat, surrounded by the mystery of night and the sounds of the jungle.  All without feeling that the animals are exploited. I took my parents there and they loved it (one of them has very high standards). The creatures of the night show and the interaction between the audience, the trainers and the animals is super fun. Expensive but well worth the expense.

Pros: night animal show was awesome.
Best time to visit 7:15PM.
While going for safari you can enjoy voice guide in your language. Just bring earphones with you.
Cons: night safari at 9:15PM is of no use, you will not be able to see all animals.

Good local pub.
Ample choices from lunch & full bistro menus. Food quality/quantity varies, depending on chefs!
Staff mostly pleasant. 
Can get busy during lunchtime hours.

For a pub the food was surprisingly good, I went for the scotch fillet and the temperature and cook was perfect. All dishes came out at the same time and the staff was friendly and helpful. They have happy hours for cocktails from 4pm till 6pm everyday and live music Fridays and Saturdays from 8pm.

I wasn’t a patron, I worked here. Was fired because the receptionist lied and stated I did not call in sick on a day I had SURGERY. Supplied hospital certificates AND proof I called in before my shift off - definitely won’t recommend this pub as the receptionist is a liar and rude to boot, not to mention the filthiest bars I’ve ever worked in, genuinely would not be surprised if they’d hardly been cleaned at all - mould growing in the glass chillers, coffee machines backed up and blocked and all the women in the office worry about is their hotel rooms.
Visited for lunch a few times, great spot! Normally have the steak and is always well cooked.
The Royal is a bit of class in Randwick. Rooms are lovely. Decor is tasteful. Food is brilliant. Lots of quiet areas during the day. Totally Re commend a Stay here.

Chips were either overcooked or sitting too long. The gravy couldn't even help  change the flavour. You need someone older with experience to help run the franchise.  A once great outlet gone down hill.
Would've been better if the sauce was on my slider & not on the paper.
Nice friendly service and quick, food was presented well, was hot and yummy.
What you'd expect. Friendly young staff.

its always something going to this place. today i ordered a zinger box, to get home and see theres no zinger burger in there. its next level. and they always overcook everything and forget to salt the chips. complaints about waiting times are true, ive seen cars lining up down the street for this place. shut it down now
Excellent hamburgers,  Fish &Chips, happy service.

I absolutely love coming here. The chips are amazing and every other item I have gotten has been nothing less than spectacular. In fact, their kebabs are the best in the area. (Substantial, well priced and No Beetroot or mince!)

Today, I decided to have a burger as I had a not-so-great experience with a burger in Oberon, NSW  a few days ago. This combo was nothing like the one I had there. The meal was substantial, the burger was cooked perfectly, the chips weren’t over cooked and I got a drink. 

Amy and Kerry always are friendly, even when it is +40° in the kitchen. They make the food perfectly every time.

Best tasting and best value beef kebabs in the whole area.  Only wish they would do chicken and lamb kebabs too.  I highly recommend food from here.  Customers just need to convince Megan about chicken and lamb.
Its the number one  take away in Tahmoor and very nice lady's work there
Nice burgers and very affordable.. loved it
Great food and friendly service. Will definitely be back.

Service over last 30 odd years has been great. But unfortunately over last 18mths or so food has been below their usual standard. Fried rice is always burnt and all meals look and taste the same. At least for take away service. Soo disappointed.
Overpriced and not that great to be honest. $35 for 2 orders. Could have got more from KFC and still have change left.
We had a delicious meal,  highly recommend  this restaurant.
The meals are nice but abit over prices we had to return one of our meals it wasn't what we order but they fixs it and made it right.

I'm a regular at Jack & Royal,  from the lunch menu to dinner & take away, the food and service are great. Fresh ingredients always used, relaxed atmosphere with a traditional decore, one of the best Thai In the area. Always recommended, it's best to make a booking on weekend evenings as they do get busy.

Such great food it is always fresh, and quick service and the staff are also nice and helpful.
5 out of 5 for them.
You won't get Thai food much better at any price. Quite fast service mostly, & can ring them for take away if you'd rather. Their ten buck lunch special is  great value. Top spot.

Have eaten in and taken away from the jack and royal a few times the services is always friendly and helpful and the food is good. Recommend that you try the crying tiger dish, its one of those meals that smells a bit off but tastes really good, you can get it as a starter so you dont have to have a large portion.
Good food & service.  Cooked to order - reasonably priced.

result.formatted_address: Shps 5 and 6, Tahmoor Town Centre Cnr Rememberence Dr and Thirlmere St, Tahmoor NSW 2573, Australia
result.name: Subway® Restaurant

reviews.text: Compared to other subways service here has been good. Foods always been comparable and typically subway. Its a nice change to maccas and meat pies but not going to win any awards from me for excellence. Fresh is best and preprocessed foods are not fresh! The market place can be difficult to get parking when busy.
Great service. Great subs!
Always happy to help, its never a hassle or worry to be ordering
Bread was burnt and the young staff were very rude. It’s a shame I have to leave a bad review but each time I go back they get worse.
Quick service

Fullerton is the hotel you go if you want to look out and see Singapore's best. Shenton Way on one side, Marina Bay on the next, the best of everything comes together here. Prices are a bit high but of course, the location is the gem here.
Great hotel. Previously the Post Office, now, it is one of the best hotels you can be in Singapore. Always have so much fun with the family when we are here.

Location is great! I really liked how it's right by the Marina Bay area, so the view is superb and very photogenic for a Singaporean hotel. It's also very accessible, being right by Raffles Place station. Lantern is great as a rooftop bar, especially at night where it's less humid and warm. Highly recommend a good date night at this place!

A beautiful hotel set in a beautiful area of Singapore on the bay. We had a corner room which was large and furnished to a high standard. The bathroom was large and well equipped with a bath and large shower and basin with lots of room for bits. The room was also equipped with a Samsung tablet providing hotel information plus a mobile phone for guest use in and out of the hotel. This hotel is popular for events and as such can cause a few problems if you wish to eat in the hotel as the restaurants can often be booked for these. On the occasion this happened to us the duty manager resolved the problem  by allowing  the brasserie menu to be served to us in the Clifford restaurant which  was a good gesture.
Visit the roof pool and enjoy good food, & drink really nice and helpful staff whilst relaxing under the sun.  Would l stay again, yes please and longer

The Fullerton Hotel is a refurbished building that was formerly called Collier Quay. It was a landing area for passenger boats going to the neighbouring Indonesian islands and junk boats ferrying goods to the bigger ships anchored offshore in the 1960/70s. Now it’s a beautiful hotel. Even if you are not a guest, it’s a beautiful place to come relax, enjoy and be near the ocean.

result.formatted_address: 2 Bayfront Avenue, B1-48, Galleria Level, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands, Singapore 018956
result.name: db Bistro & Oyster Bar by Daniel Boulud

reviews.text: One of the best oyster bar in Singapore. The ambiance is great also, it's not crowded and has good views. Happy oyster hour is great time to get half-off price, starting from from 3pm to 6pm on Monday to Friday except holiday. I just came here twice but will be coming here on next trip.

Very good service & tasty food. My sea bass was cooked to perfection. Chef’s assorted dessert was to die for. Looking forward to dine again.
One thing which was really disturbing us was the bad & loud Music. Please play a nice calming music.

Came here for our dinner before the musical and the food, drinks and service is excellent. The braised beef is so tender and juicy, the McGuigan Merlot is good and the service is the best. Highly recommended.
Best signature dB burger.. It was so delicious and big size.. Leftover the fries due to already stomach full... Highly recommended... There is also oyster hours for you to grab!..

One of my favourites in Singapore!
I remember first eating here for my 18th birthday years ago and had a most memorable seafood platter with my grandparents and my best friend for a late lunch.

Years later, I am happy to note that the seafood lived up to my expectations, given that it has been a long time since I've last visited Singapore. I also had the great tuna tartare!

One of the most beautiful hotels in the world situated in prime location providing great views from every angle, this architectural masterpiece is well worth a visit. I can recommend to spend the evening walking around the harbor, Merlion Park, Singapore Flyer and then walk along the water way to Sand's and head for the skybar located at the roof with unbeatable views of this fantastic city of lights!!

Fantastic, spectacular and wonderful views from this iconic building in Singapore. You have to pay a fee to get the lift to the observeration area but it is certainly worth it. Can say anything about the actual hotel as I could not afford to stay there but I expect it is a top quality place to lay your head for a few nights.

A very basic but great place to watch a performance. Came here to watch the musical Mama Mia. The performance was good and the sound system was superb. There was no distortion even the sound was loud. The seats and the layout were done well. There were good directional signage except the toilets are limited and long queues resulted.

A modern, beautiful and comfortable theater giving the audience total entertainment experience.

We were there to watch the Lion King Musical Concert which was a beautiful concert. The experience was given added values with the well designed theater. 

The place was spacious giving everyone irrespective of sitting position to have the best possible view. Seats were comfortable and spacious enough to not bump into audience on both sides, yet not being blocked by the one sitting in front. 

The only problem is only one toilet available for the audience to rush to during the break!
Awesome venue. Was there for Lion King

Novotel Singapore is located in the heart of Clarke Quay, which is a popular area for tourists to stay. It is very well connected via MRT, Bus and Taxi services, and surrounded by a lot of popular restaurant serving different cuisines. 
The hotel itself is also pretty nice with spacious and clean rooms, courteous and helpful staff and extremely child friendly. The breakfast buffet has a lot to chose from, especially and Indian section to cater to guests from India.  
The hotel gives an overall pleasant feel to the guests.
The location and ambience is good. There is swimming and gym. U can enjoy the locality view if u happen to get the right rooms.

Reasonable hotel for a few days.
Breakfast with large variaty, but food is of average quality only.
Fruit with almost no taste and I ate only once worse waffles. 
Rooms are fine; silent, good in size and we'll equipped.
The next Metro and bus stop is only 150m away.

4-star hotel but overall 3-star level.
Room is not renovated recently.
There were 3 of coin laundry machine and dryers. 
If you stay at premier floor, you can access the premier lounge where enjoy the snack and beverages. However, I recommend to have the breakfast in the restaurant of 7th floor. 
Very good location where you can Clarke Quay by foot.

Great place in Singapore center. Wonderful skyline view from business lounge on 24th floor. Perfect for family King bed suite. Great people, great service. As little minus, slightly worn furniture in a room, but it doesn't change very positive impression.

The worst 5 stars hotel I have ever stayed!  I stayed for 4 nights and here are some thoughts. 
1. The breakfast and lunch is the exact same everyday like a dormitory.
2. The room is quite odors sometimes
3. The first night the air condition is not cool.  Technician came and said that I should wait for it to get cooler.  Ended up that the next day I repeated my request and it gets fixed.
4.  The check-out is hectic part.. Slow and too little staffs.
5.  The parking at the lobby is bad managed.. Someone park and left the van in front of the lobby main door.. Make it difficult for taxis and grab to gets in.

Never come back ever again.
Five star hotel in Singapore.. Good to stay for tourism, I really like these food.. Good view from my room and also good service anything in here.. So dont hesitate to booking. Thank you
Very upmarket  hotel. Not sure if it's for the average but traveller. Comfy rooms and swanky hotel foyer.  More suited to Asian travellers.

Good location with helpful and friendly staff. Quiet rooms and well maintained. My only issue was the breakfast buffet which served very little hot 'western' type food which was obvious following previous visit when it had been available.

This is a good hotel with wonderful staff. The location on the river seemed like a good idea but it is too far from metro services and this is my reason for the 3 stars. If you're just there for hanging out in the evening and don't look to sight seeing it is a great hotel for you.

Fantastic, climate controlled multi level garden with sample gardens from all over the world. Don't miss this and the Flower Dome nearby if you are visiting Singapore. Especially recommended for older folks and children. Great natural experience in these days of plastic/synthetic fun in most outdoor locations/amusement parks.

Do not miss !! Very enriching connect with the nature experience !!! Awesome variety of flora and fauna. Winding up pathway.....centered around an artificially created hill . Amazing upkeep. Feel great that the Earth was originally like this.  Harsh reminder for all of us preserve , whatever is left of it now. Very inspiring, invigorating walk. My family loved this. Worth the effort !!! Worth every penny !!!

Great. The Cloud Forest is higher but slightly smaller at 0.8 hectares (2.0 acres). It replicates the cool moist conditions found in tropical mountain regions, found in South-East Asia, Middle- and South America. It features a 138 ft "Cloud Mountain", accessible by an elevator, and visitors will be able to descend the mountain via a circular path where a 115 ft waterfall provides visitors with refreshing cool air. Very nice and rare to see such arrangements of plants and trees as vertical garden inside temperature controlled closed glass dome. Good view while walking down the walk-way from the hill top. Lift is provided to reach the top. Rare miniature plants are grown inside glass bottles through magnifying glass provided.

This absolutely beautiful. It's definitely a top attraction for anyone, local or tourist. There are all sorts of flora on display here on the different levels, and it's fun to go up into the highest reaches to start your journey. Definitely a good place to go if you're looking for something to do.

At Gardens by the Bay there are two indoor gardens or dome. Cloud Forest is one of them. Architectural view and environment looks very good. You will feel that you are in a different environment. You will be able to the multi level amazing attraction including artificial waterfall and different types of plants. You will be refreshed after visiting the Cloud Forest.

If you don't know what to do in your spare time on the trip, chose this flyer! One can't just go wrong with this. You get to see the mesmerizing  landscape of entire Singapore along with a guided interactive infotainment system.
Nice and huge Ferris wheel in Singapore. A major tourist attraction. Can get a bird eye view of whole Singapore. The wheel rotates slowly and takes about 30-40 min to complete a rotation.
Great tourist attraction in Singapore! We went up at sunset, it was beautiful to watch the sun setting over the city. Would highly recommend!

It was really cool to be on the second tallest Ferris wheel in the world! It gave a great view of The Marina Bay Sands Hotel, Gardens By The Bay, the Art Science Museum, the Singapore city skyline and so much more as well. It was amazing to go on.

A relaxing way to kill an hour of your time (the time on the Flyer itself is about 30 minutes).  The views even when your capsule has not yet reached the top are still quite spectacular, and the voice-over video on the various screens inside does a good job of pointing out and describing the various landmarks.

One of my favorite places in Sentosa. The flowrider is one of the best I've used. The instructors are super friendly and really great at teaching you to use it. The bar itself is quite nice. Very good food and drinks.

Very fun as a first timer. How much you learn depends on the instructor you get. My instructor seemed aloof at first but started sharing tips after a few failed attempts. Go early to avoid a packed class, which reduce your number of tries. There were 6 in my class and i did around 7 tries, more than I expected!
Lots of fun. Mentors are good and very attentive. Just prepare to be sore at the end of it especially if you fall often.

It's great fun to ride these artificial waves and there's only a few of them around the world.
The only thing that seriously spoiled the fun were the guys operating the attraction (you couldn't call them 'instructors'): they were pretty uninterested, tired of their job, counting their precious time till their next break, like they wished they were somewhere else. 
Too bad because this attraction was pretty pricey.
Nice beach time. Good music, could be quieter. Order food only if you are extremely hungry.

Great resort island with lots of museums, amusement areas and shopping.  Excellent restaurants.  Clean and spacious.  Easy access to beach with water sports activities.  Quick access with tram, bus and private transportation.  Has nice hotels to stay.  Very safe.  Great customer services.  Beautiful landscape with jogging and biking trails.  Lots of shading areas and rest stops.

In resort world santosa there are lots of activities goes on & on. The atmosphere is so good & free that i think every one can enjoy in one's own way. Rides; shows; restaurants; eating outlets ; just being  there is enjoyable in its own way. There shows on streets & gather there ,sit or stand & enjoy. I found the shows were perfect in spreading their message whatever they want to convey. Enjoy the creations of nature in S.E.A aquarium & man made ride in universal studios. Just get in .

Fantastic family resort, beautifully constructed and themed. Can be a bit much and it's definitely bigger than most people think. Food and drinks can be pricey especially around Universal Studious. There's a mall on the opposite side where you get the Sentosa Express from. Get food there if you don't want to spend too much on the island. Worth a visit, there are parts that will cost you nothing to visit, like the beach.

Visited after going to the aquarium. Whilst the place is very clean and tidy, there are plenty of restaurants but that's it. Lacks any real vibe, seems very plastic and false. Monorail was very handy though. There is a real lack of signage or anyone around to ask questions.
Great experience.. must visit if you are an adventurous soul and like fun rides. Luge was the most fun.. you can race with friends and see who gets the best control and speed.

result.formatted_address: 2 Bayfront Avenue, 01 - 81 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands, Singapore 018956
result.name: Bread Street Kitchen Singapore

reviews.text:
Great.....

Very good food. I regret that I ordered the beef Wellington though. The Wellington was tasty but three slice was more than enough for me. The waitress was very nice and professional. Had a taste of my sisters fish and chips. It was the bomb! That was the best fish and chips I had ever had.

Went down to check out pie week. Took 2 stars off as I was pretty disappointed with the food. I had the steak & marrow pie. It was tiny for $42 and the meat was salty. I could not enjoy most of the crust as it was stuck to the bowl & I made a huge mess trying to pry the pastry off. I just gave up. The service here was excellent & hence some stars. Servers were attentive and served with a smile. Personally for me it's 2 stars for food & 5 stars for service

Thank you chef Steven for making our day. Great food. Amazing friendly staff 😎 wow thanks for the reply BSK. 

Also a big shout out to the two bartenders. One gentleman I believe his name starts with R, was so welcoming we ended up staying past brunch till tea time. Hats off to him. We will be back.

Very overpriced for the quality of food unfortunately.  Staff were excellent though. Good location at Marina Bay, although the view is currently blighted by building works outside.

Edited: after the reply by the management - a standard reply obviously.  The fact remains that the food was very disappointing.  As a specific example, the pie was recommended but it was basically a purchase of thin air.

One of these pies that has a crispy puff pastry lid with almost nothing but air underneath.  The pie filling was not deep enough to reach the end of the fork tines,  that was how little was served.  The taste was ok, not bad but you've definitely tasted better in an average pub.

It'd be interesting to witness the reaction of Mr Ramsey if he was served such food on one of his shows.
The wait can be a bit long. Pls have a reservation to guarantee seating. Food is good but not that good. Cool place to hang out. Very friendly service excellent.

result.name: Fu Qing Marina Bay Seafood Restaurant

reviews.text: Check Trip Advisor for a more comprehensive review on this infamous place. The only reason to eat here if you want to get scammed of your money. Feeling rich and wanna to this taste some lousy food? This is the place to be!
Very expensive. Small portions and watery beer

Expensive place. Not the best food. But view and seating area is good. This place is suitable for tourist who yet to appreciate local cusine. Wont go there again. Customer service can be alot improved. Sprite can cost 7 bucks.
good view but bad food and expensive price. fried squid is oily and soggy. how can u go wrong with such simple food. dont come unless have no choice.

Keep away from this place! We’ve made a big mistake , it is a try ripoff they lure you by telling you Chile crab is $50 per kg, then distract you and offer Alaskan King crab, not making you aware the price increases to $198 per kg. Very expensive not nice food not good service! Don’t waste your time!!!

result.formatted_address: 6 Raffles Blvd, #04-600 Marina Mandarin Hotel, Singapore 039594
result.name: Sushi Jiro At Marina Mandarin

reviews.text: A very standard place. Chawanmushi was grainy. All else competent. Good but overpriced. I can see a greedy owner watching chef on CCTV so not too much ikura is dished out

Had a 5 star wonderful experience dinner at one of the top fine dining Japanese restaurant in Singapore. The exquisite foods were skillfully and freshly prepared by the Executive Chef Mr Kenji Nakagawa. One of my top recommendations for Japanese food!

Everything is perfect.Awesome appetizer, Tempura, Sashimi, Sushi, Customer service.
If you come to Singapore, you should definitely visit this restaurant!!
I visited for lunch and had Hiyama beef katsu and steak recommended by chef. It was so nice and I recommend strongly for you if you've never been.
Wide variety of sashimi that are not readily available in sg

Lovely hotel not far from Bugs street. Great staff, awesome breakfast. Gm is good enough for those who like to keep fit. Handy for transport links and always good to be staying with a brand you can trust!
It’s what you would expect, they don’t disappoint. Excellent facility/room. Flawless. Very reasonably priced considering the location, facility and service.

Very nice hotel with an excellent staff. 

The decor is lovely...colonial. The restaurants are decent. I preferred the food at the Ritz but then again, different ballpark. 

I would stay here again.
compact modern room. disappointing breakfast spread (variety, taste, quality). gym is not equipped with weights above 14kg.
Attending wedding lunch.   The food there are very nice.  I like it very much.

This hotel exceeded my expectations in every department. The highlight is the food served in the restaurants. Every single dish I ordered had something extra in terms of flavor that surprised me.  I can't wait to come back. Staff is so professional and courteous.

Quite a mixed review to be honest. Planned a surprise proposal for my girlfriend. VIP services upgraded me to a skyline suite, experienced fantastic service.. however this was dampened by their poor handling of parking coupons. Asked for parking coupons for my guests but was outrightly rejected with a 1 coupon per room policy reason. Had to explain to my guests which put me in a spot. Was told by concierge that Pan Pacific guests faced this issue before, but they didn't seemed to have structured a solution quickly to solve it. Eventually I reimbursed my guests myself to save the waiting time. Looks like paying for a suite doesn't get you a guaranteed 5 star service. FYI, I have never faced this at other local hotels before.

We stayed 3 nights in this hotel. The room was spacious, with nice bay view at the balcony. There are many restaurants in the hotel, food is fine. Hotel is connected to many shopping centers. Concierge is very professional and friendly. We had a good time!
Outstanding hotel in the heart of the business district. Elegant finishing of the rooms and interior. Incredible restaurants and very friendly and dedicated staff

One of favorites in Singapore. Started staying here from 2005 and stayed couple of times. Rooms are large and spacious, clean and staffs are simply amazing. I remember about one fine morning when we were late to have breakfast and it was closed, however, the staffs arranged some good breakfast for us even after hours. Will never forget this service of PanPac Singapore.

This is a place that has such history and the architecture is so detailed. The sculptures decorating the temple are fantastic. Also you have the opportunity to go in there. For women, you have to have your head covered when you go in. It has a calming feeling when you sit in there.

Im not familiar with their culture or religious beliefs i just found it interesting to visit because of those printed ceiling, very unique design of the temple. Other than that i would be giving it 5 stars if i know the story behind those relics over the temples entrance door

Definitely a great sensory experience. The temple has great design and decor. The sounds are fantastic with vocal and instrumental offerings to the deities. The unique smells that one can only experience in a ritual setting and the tastes of the offerings that the devotees make available. All in all, a great way to experience the hindu culture of devotion.
Visiting Mariamman temple is thrilling in a foreign land. Well maintained. Architecture is fine with masonry details. People of all religion visit it.

it was really a great experience seeing the evening prayers ceremony. We have also been offered food (prasad) which was tasty and they welcomed us like they (who sponsored the prayers) know us. It was amazing to see the south Indian traditions. 

Even i have been in Indian from the last 30 years but never got a chance to see such a ceremony inside a temple.

Full of people, houses, stores, fast food restaurants, at places - interesting architecture; Chinese lanterns all over. Well worth a visit to soak up in Far Eastern culture, though in Singapore everything is a little bit different ... When we visited, it was the Chinese New  Year, so a lot of decorations were spread all over.

Not the usual Chinatown around the world.  It's not as dirty since its Singapore.  Food market is now closed but the street is still packed with varieties of option.  Shop around if you're looking for souvenirs.  Price difference between shops are common. Overall it's a nice to spend 3 hours there.

Good place for buying souvenir and having NON VEG Chinese food and other foods. Mainly Beef, pork, duck, various sea foods, etc. Buddha Tooth Relic is a good Buddhist temple in China town. Many shops are wholesale kind.

So many food options! And outdoor covered seating which is nice. Take a walk around and find something that suits your tastes! It can get a little busy but just don't worry and you'll be eating in no time. Lots of gift shops with junk as well.
Focus on the tourist is noticeable from every corner but even with that it's still unique and worth visiting. Try to go to hawker center there after sunset. There's little pub to discover.

This class was recommend by my niece. It was run & enjoyable & a great learning experience. If you are an experienced or novice cook you will enjoy & get something out of this class. i loved learning about the history behind the heritage foods. Being a former Singaporean I am familiar with Singapore food & the dishes we made were really delicious & authentic. Helen is an engaging teacher. I am looking forward to returning for another lass & highly recommend it to others seeking a fun culinary adventure in Singapore.

I've never been to a cooking class while I'm love to cooking.
The course was fabulous not only in cooking but in discovering the history of the country... 
Teresa our extraordinary teacher, she told us, and explained how to cook as my grandmother or my mother would have done with the same passion. 
I will definitely take part in the next course, to talk and gain the experience that the teachers of FOOD PLAYGROUND have !!!!!
Is too interesting and fun. A big thank you to everyone !!

Great to get back to Food Playground after doing a great class here 4 yrs ago. Love that you get a hands on cooking experience while learning about the food culture and history of Peranakan food in Singapore. Mary was a terrific tutor sharing her own family experience and upbringing. 
Daniel (owner) is the champion of this meaningful social cause, which is to help more stay-at-home mothers return to the workforce by providing them with meaningful flexible employment opportunities so they can stay connected to society, earn some income for their family and regain their self-confidence. 
Highly recommended as the first thing to do during any stay in the lion city!

One of the best parts of our Singapore vacation! Intimate cooking class where we learned about the history of Singapore dishes while making our own. Great whether you are a beginner or a professional.

Wonderful experience and a tremendous way to spend a morning in Singapore'. Teresa was our instructor and not only did she teach us cooking techniques but also the history of the dishes we made. She had an excellent way of presenting her subject and adding humorous personal tidbits made for a very easy and tasty learning experience. I would recommend this @session to anyone who is visiting Singapore and wants to understand the culture and food. You won't be disappointed.

Don't go by its size or location. The service isn't not to your expectations, beyond to what you think! Great service and staff. Fantastic experience I have. Just drop and feel like you are at your another home. I have ever seen such homely food in any abroad place so far. You can't compare either breakfast, lunch or dinner with such combination of food items. My rating is not five 🌟 but 5 🌟+++++.☝.
Great place to stay at Little India. Rooms are extraordinarily beautiful. Provides basic amenities like toiletries, slippers, electric kettle, mini fridge etc. Superb breakfast buffet.

The rooms were rather small, but was clean. The staff were helpful and it was close to the Metro and local eateries. Perfect place if you like Indian or Pakistani food; decent neighborhood as well. Recommend for couples, travelers on a budget or in transit.

Perfect location for Indian tourists. The staff was very polite and the humility was exceptional. The hotel was very helpful and understanding to personal needs. Very happy with the overall experience.
Too good & clean ..... Staff is very good.... 😍food is  testy.. Love it..

Very decent place to stay. Clean and near to public transportation. But rooms are small. No designated wardrobes and no proper space to open you suitcase. 
But pool is good with chilling vibes. 
Very friendly staff and fairly close to the station

Pros :
Perfect location.
All the famous spots are nearby.
Cabs are available all the time.
Great swimming pool.
Great buffet spread.
Friendly and professional stuffs.

Cons : Room was so cramped. Feels like you are inside a box. No cupboard.

Very good hotel. 10-20 minutes from the airport. Very quick service for check in and checkout. Not good for Asian or South Asian people in respect to food in breakfast. Rooms are a little small but good if you are roaming around the city in the day. Markets and shopping center are in walking distance.

Good clean hotel. 
The rooms are small as we have come to expect in Singapore. Though there r no cupboards/ wardrobes, but the spaces were designed efficiently and attention to details ensured that  end user requirements were taken care of. Like the locker was provided in a drawer, a rod under a slab and hooks on the wall compensated for the absence of the wardrobe. A play area for children. A small gym and a good sized lap pool. 
Spacious lobby with ample seating arrangement. A gloria Jean's coffee shop. A good, reasonably priced  Indian restaurant, grocery store, and some other restaurant in addition to the hotel restaurant. 
Taxi available at the hotel lobby all the time. 
The rooms facing the outside have got good city view while the ones facing the internal courtyard may not offer a great view.

Average hotel with very small rooms. Did not stay here, but was visiting a friend and saw the rooms. Very small rooms! The reception area looks big and gives a good feeling about the hotel, however rooms are very small. Location is good! Not much to tell about the staff as I was just there for couple of hours.

Nice place to stay. Strategically located. But not exactly worth the price paid for. Rooms are on the smaller side. My room had minor traffic noise despite sealed windows. Price defines it as luxurious, but facilities could ve been better for price paid.
Great hotel in the heart of Singapore near all amenities and eating places. Can be noisy down stairs but rooms of very good standard. Breakfast very poor

Perfect reasonable hotel for stay.
Food is also delicious, they do have Indian food on the menu.
It is located perfectly for tourists.

Pleasant and proactive staff. Clean, tidy and well kept public areas. Near to several Hawker centres. Across the road to an Aladdin's cave of all manner of clothing, accessories and outfits from the Indian subcontinent. A short walking distance to a MRT stop.

Nice hotel but bedrooms fairly small with nowhere to sit except on the bed.  Close to Little India area of Singapore.  In room fridge was so iced up I doubt it would have kept anything cool, however when we mentioned it at reception it was sorted within a few hours.

Decent dim sum. A lot of the nicer food were mixed with truffle. Service here was a bit slow as they seem short staffed for a hotel Chinese restaurant. It is expensive to eat here so would expect better service. There are some discounts available such as for amex love dining but other than that at full price it's not really worth

A restaurant that has good Lou Hei - not so sweet. The roasted chicken was nice and tender. The other dishes are so so. The attention of the service staff is not too bad. Generally a good place to go since it’s not as crowded as other restaurant.
Nice environment, very good and delicious Dim Sum.  They also served Peking Duck.
Had to book 2 days in advance, extremely slow service, nothing fantastic about the food, not worth the time and price. Definitely not returning.

The menu has changed and dim sum is no longer a standalone menu but rather has been incorporated into the main menu. There are now only about 10 items in the dim sum menu and prices have increased tremendously as well. 

The food still taste good but given the price increase, it does certainly leave a bit of a bitter taste to many customers. Having said that if you have AMEX Platinum Card or better, you can get great discounts of up to 50% off (excluding GST and service charge)
