reviews.text: My husband enjoyed more than I did. It was not a very long trip and we were talked into a bus tour of the island as a add on to the ticket. The upside of the bus tour was learning the historical significance of the island. The island is basically a theme park with Disney type rides, a casino, a Universal park, it has a beach that looked inviting but we were jet lagged from a 24 hour flight, and not dressed for swimming.

Unfortunately the cable car is too hot. I asked the staff before the doors of the cable car closed if it would cool down. They said yes the fan is on. Well it didn't. I used my hand fan but that wasn't enough. When I reached the Sentosa stop I went to the ticket counter and asked for a refund for the return. I was told that I couldn't receive a refund because, I rode the cable car. Of course I wouldn't have ridden it if the staff had said the temperature would NOT cool down. I don't like to post non-positive reviews but, as a traveler this is information I would have found important before I had made my decision to take the Singapore Cable Car.

Get round trip tickets for value for money ! That way, you can explore the island on foot and hop on the cable car when the feet starts to ache. The souvenir shops are awesome..the gifts sold are thoughtful and cater to all ages, from a foldable walking cane to plush toys for the young ones! If only there was a commentary in the cable car, it would be even better!

It was an unique thrilling experience of riding by a cable car. We bought round tickets which helped us to explore many stations on ground including Sentosa island. Sentosa Island has many transport modes of reaching from the Mainland. 

There are many attractions at each of the stations including restaurants and tourists’ facilities. Beautiful picturesque surroundings and one can take lot of photos for remembrance. We thoroughly enjoyed the cable car ride.

Very nice experience. A must visit for tourists. One of the ways to enter Sentosa island. Make sure you cover all the stations and morning and evening times. Do visit Faber peak as cable car is the fastest and easiest way to go there. It runs till 9:30 in night so plan accordingly.

Favourite tea time place to go to for us. Grab a few of my friends, parking is good with the valet. It is unbelievable that we are in the city, and it is so peaceful and quiet. Calm staff helps in the whole relaxing experience. Love this place. After going there a few times, the staff knows you by name. Amazing.

Beautiful both inside and out! Great restaurants and a great point to start a pleasant walk along the water front. I imagine in the evenings it's a great place to see the lights from what is otherwise considered a party area in Singapore (Clarke quay/boat quay) would recommend at least a wander around the area!!!
Very nice hotel. Attended a wedding banquet at their straits room. Very grand and beautiful settings. The atmosphere, food, service were all fantastic. Spend some time looking at the architecture.

The staff make every stay a real pleasure. They are so caring, attentive and generous with their time. The hotel is in a great location near the city if you’re working or good bars and restaurants if you’re unwinding after a long day of meetings, shopping or just need to unwind some more. If I was into traditional architecture I probably would score it 5 stars. The building is grand and spacious. For me, I’d like more contemporary design and art but that’s not for everyone.

Went to enjoy my buffet feast for lunch. Not bad. Service staffs is friendly, great atmosphere, price is reasonably good under 1 for 1 promo by credits card. Japanese sushi is great but came too late to know that we actually can request salmon belly.. Overall awesome experience. 😊👍They even throw in a small birthday cake for me, sing a birthday song.. ✨ 🔊 😄

One place not to miss in Singapore. Relatively inexpensive, we went to the future exhibition only, however there was also a minimalist one on too. It was amazing, there were interactive kinetic digital exhibitions where people could interact with the projected images. You could also draw pictures, scan them in and they would be generated on the wall. Great for grown up travellers and also those with kids. Check out the light installation too!

Good place which displays art in way that you could have never thought before. It has different exhibits throughout the year, you can check the schedule before going. Friendly staff with easy and efficient ticketing options. Plus they have a cafe and a beautiful lily pond around. Must go.

It is one of the must go places in Singapore. This particular exhibit: the Future World is best for children. They have 2 interactive exhibit that the kids would surely love. The most breathtaking exhibit for me is the Crystal Galaxy, it really is a must see. It is like you're taken to another dimension.

One of the best touristic attraction in Singapore.  It's at Marina bay and close to many other amazing attractions. Its impressive architecture is itself a big attraction. Inside there are many interesting exhibition to all ages. Enjoy!

We went for FUTURE WORLD - WHERE ART MEETS SCIENCE.

5 stars for children and 3 stars for adults. I am awed by the presentation, the level of advanced smart technology and how interactive the setting was. The price was a little steep but it was worth it.

The place however is more like a child’s world. For an adult, it is like a scratch of curiosity. Nonetheless, HIGHLY RECOMMENDED FOR A FAMILY OUTING.

Pretty nice place. Just need a few minutes to see it however since it is not very extensive, but pleasant nevertheless. We got a ticket for this as part of a combo ticket, so not sure the actual cost, but certainly worth a few dollars to see. We went in the day, and were pleased, but I think it would be great in day or night. Really nice, but very small. Given how iconic it is for Singapore I would say it is a must see. and it is beautiful at night.
Super garden of the future. You can see how much care and planning has gone into this place. The enclosures are sublime. Great! Must visit!

Spend half day if you really want to enjoy the whole garden bu the bay.visit OCBC Skyway during almost evening to catch a sunset and lights play in the evening.you need to pay if you want to enter this bridge.total combo with  the garden by the flower dome around 30sgd.

Its windy since its quiet high on top of the skyway,be careful and be mindful there.

You can stand at the each corner if you want to do sightseeing but remember during busy hour they will limit your visit time there.better go on weekday if you have time.

If you don't fear heights or if you don't suffer from Vertigo, this is one of the best tourist attractions you shouldn't miss. To get to the skyway, there is a wait time, as there is a maximum capacity it can handle. But it is worth the wait. You get a wonderful feeling and nice photo shoot opportunities. Don't miss it.

One of the best tourist spots in Singapore with free entry. We went there and paid a few bucks for Christmas wonderland and it was good. Twilight view of the super tree is just awesome while music show is just as good. It tends to be crowded with many tourists but at least the crowd control was okay.

The history and artwork displayed in the National Gallery is a beautiful and impressive collection. The tourist tickets were 20SD but we were able to get them online for only 14. Spent over 2 hours viewing the multiple galleries and could have spent even more time if we had wanted to see it all. I highly recommend all visitors make this at least a half day of your trip itinerary!

I joined the free tour that was offered by the museum. The docent was such a gem. She shared so much about the history behind the building's architecture, and it's function as a supreme court years ago. It makes me appreciate the paintings to a different level when she shared more about the artist and also the story behind each painting. Great experience. Will definitely visit again.

A nice place to spend approximately half a day. Very beautiful exhibits and the building is huge. It's easy to miss out on some beautiful art if you can't figure out the navigation inside. I went on a Saturday when the entry happened to be free and it wasn't very crowded. You can enjoy the exhibits and pop into one of their many restaurants. I was surprised to find good food for a pretty decent amount in one of the cafes.

Husband works next to this place at the Supreme Courts so this place is my coffee fix or waiting area till he is off work. Sit around, or walk the galleries. Very very relaxing and good fun. It used to be the old Supreme Courts and wow, they have really preserved this place really well. Well done.

I went to see the Minimalist Exhibition before it ends soon. Thoroughly enjoyed, go in the morning when it opens as you'll have more of the exhibits to yourself. I already find the staff very helpful and if you live in Singapore, sign up to be a Gallery Insider, it's definitely worth it, as you can go back as many times as you like.

Incredible show. Beautiful light and water display accompanied by some great music.. Get there early in order to grab a spot to sit otherwise you'll be standing for quite a while and risk not seeing much. Free to watch and there's plenty of places to eat and shop nearby so you can easily make a night of it.

Spectra how much I love YOU!!!!

WOW, what a breathtaking and mindblowing kind of show.

This is definitely any type of water show, the music, the colors, the lights, and everything else made this a wonderful show.

We went twice and if it wasn't I was sick, we would have gone 4 times.

I loved it so much, it made me happy and I got such a positive vibe out if it.

This show is located on the water and you can watch it from the main entrance of the Shops at Marina Bay Sands.

A free laser light show in front of The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands. It was the first time I saw one of this laser shows in my life and I must say it`s absolutely amazing. If you are travelling to Singapore this is a must do, the show just outside of The Shoppes Mall. I will definitely watch the show again on my next visit.

A very nice laser show. They spray water into the air and project videos in that water. You can hear music and all in all it is a very nice show. Make sure you come early as there are many people who want to see that and if you are stuck in the crowd you do not see much. The show takes about 15 minutes and they do it twice per evening.

I was in owe while watching the light show. A spectacular night to remember.   I think I almost cried just by watching this water light dances. This will just melt your heart. A night you should not miss and did I mentioned?? it's FREE.

This dome is beautiful. There's a massive array of beautiful flowers here from all over the world. It can be quite busy, but it is still completely worth the visit. Some lovely photo opportunities here as well.
Best of all, it is completely air-conditioned!

Pretty flowers. Cherry blossoms display when I was there. I went late evening, it was not crowded and such a nice and easy browse at a your own pace. Also easy for photos taking although for some parts, had to queue for your turn. 
Will  be bringing overseas friend in May when the tulips will be duty.

Rarest collections of flowering plants from all over the world !!! Nurtured and presented in a controlled environment dome. My wife thoroughly enjoyed being a gardening enthusiast. Very inspiring...makes all of us to determined to do a lot more to sustainability !!! Passionate volunteers around to explain the nuances of every plant / flower. My family enjoyed thoroughly. Worth every penny !!! Worth every effort !!!

Really love this masterpiece! I think it is a mandatory place to visit in Singapore. With only S$ 28 you can get in to Flower Dome and Cloud Forest at Gardens by the Bay. You can see the beauty of nature, feel the fresh air you can't get in the city, and see the plants from many countries. You'll love nature more after you go here. I just love the architecture, the air, the plants, and ... Everything inside!

The flower dome has so many different varieties of trees, sussion plants and port flower in the garden. The theme changes every few months and you also found new season of flowers from all over the world. It's a bit cold inside and just nice compare with the weather outside. Great to visit with friends and families and have a great day out !

Definitely worth visiting the Majestic Merlion.  This is much bigger than the Merlion in the main city. The view of the Merlion is surreal with water bodies surrounding it and lush green all around it. Must see if you are visiting Sentosa Island in Singapore. The island is the perfect destination for tourists especially.

Interior was nice on the ground level. The lucky token was a nice idea. The views were good but it was way too crowded and not worth the wait on the narrow stairway. The lucky bell was also way too loud for such a tiny confined space. I would recommend the cable car if you want views of the island.

Definitely come here during the weekdays.  Much less people and hence much easier to take pictures without tons of people around.   Then walk is nice as long as you come here in the afternoon while the sun is setting.  Sea breeze definitely helps to cool you down a bit.   Prepare to do tons of walking unless you are paying for the monorails.

This place was very enjoyable. Pay one time SGD $4 for the train to the island then you can travel free inside the island by train or tram. Everything here is just well designed, clean, beautiful and interesting.

Sentosa Merlion! A place to take a good couple of snaps and thats about it. Don’t even bother taking a trip up the top. There is nothing to see and a sheer waste of money. Usually there are some nice song and dance performance below near the Merlion monorail station

Very good place for kids to visit

Magic experience for the young and the not so young.

Great experience. It is thrilling but not dangerous at the same time.

We got the 3 course ticket and thought it was enough. 

It can get really hot in the daytime, so I recommend you to go after 5PM. (Although it might be more crowded)

This is a fun experience. Everyone enjoys it. I just wish i could take unlimited rides.
